                           \n                                \n                                \n                                                \n            \n        \n    \n        \n                                                                                                                                                                    \n            \n    \n    \n        \n                    \n                        \n                                    \n\n\n\n\u003cdiv id=\"article-body\" itemprop=\"articleBody\"\u003e\u003cdiv id=\"custom_block_0\"\u003e\n\u003ch3\u003eSummary\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cdiv\u003e \n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e Pixel phones could get a new feature that makes it easier to pay using Google Wallet. \u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e The Android 16 DP2 release reveals that Google could be working on a double-tap gesture that will bring up Wallet. \u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e Since this is just in the code, it\u0026#39;s unclear when and if this feature will even launch. \u003c/li\u003e\n \u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eGoogle Wallet has become a completely different beast over the past couple of years, offering a safe and secure way to store not only your credit and debit cards, \u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/google-wallet-digital-id-us-passports-available-now/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003ebut also your ID, passport\u003c/a\u003e, music tickets, transit cards, and more. In addition to this, Wallet has also continued to \u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/google-wallet-adds-support-for-18-new-banks-nov-2024/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eexpand support for more banks\u003c/a\u003e, adding more and more financial institutions each month.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv data-include-community-rating=\"false\" id=\"a59b-4a98-903767b99426\" data-nosnippet=\"\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/ways-to-improve-google-wallet/\"\u003e\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-09-20-14-44-02-1.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-09-20-14-44-02-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=422\u0026amp;h=268\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-09-20-14-44-02-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=422\u0026amp;h=268\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-09-20-14-44-02-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=310\u0026amp;h=220\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-09-20-14-44-02-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=310\u0026amp;h=220\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-09-20-14-44-02-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=720\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-09-20-14-44-02-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=720\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-09-20-14-44-02-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-09-20-14-44-02-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003cimg width=\"3000\" height=\"1688\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"A stylized photo of a hand reaching into a wallet.\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-09-20-14-44-02-1.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-09-20-14-44-02-1.jpg\"/\u003e \u003c/picture\u003e \u003c/figure\u003e \u003c/div\u003e \u003c/a\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan data-field=\"label\"\u003eRelated\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003ch5\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/ways-to-improve-google-wallet/\" title=\"5 things that should be changed on Google Wallet ASAP\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e 5 things that should be changed on Google Wallet ASAP \u003c/a\u003e \u003c/h5\u003e\u003cp\u003eThese five changes would greatly improve the digital wallet app\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/div\u003e \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eOf course, Google Wallet isn\u0026#39;t perfect and there are \u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/ways-to-improve-google-wallet/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003esome changes we\u0026#39;d love to see in 2025\u003c/a\u003e, but for the most part, things are pretty good as they are for now. With that said, it looks like a new update could be on the horizon that will make it easier and faster to access Wallet. The new feature is not available yet but has appeared in \u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/android-16-developer-preview-2/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eAndroid 16 Developer Preview 2\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"easy-access-to-wallet-at-the-press-of-a-button\"\u003e Easy access to Wallet at the press of a button \u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/10/google-wallet-pay-hero.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/10/google-wallet-pay-hero.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/10/google-wallet-pay-hero.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/10/google-wallet-pay-hero.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/10/google-wallet-pay-hero.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/10/google-wallet-pay-hero.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/10/google-wallet-pay-hero.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/10/google-wallet-pay-hero.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/10/google-wallet-pay-hero.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003cimg width=\"4080\" height=\"2720\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Google Wallet on a Pixel resting on top of a black Visa card.\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/10/google-wallet-pay-hero.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/10/google-wallet-pay-hero.jpg\"/\u003e \u003c/picture\u003e \u003c/figure\u003e \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eMishaal Rahman of \u003ca href=\"https://www.androidauthority.com/double-tap-power-google-wallet-3513029/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eAndroid Authority\u003c/a\u003e was able to uncover this new feature by looking through the current developer preview. While there aren\u0026#39;t any direct features, Rahman discovered a new configuration \u0026#34;\u003cstrong\u003ewalletDoubleTapPowerGestureEnabled\u003c/strong\u003e\u0026#34;. Rahman shares that this new configuration will allow users to double tap the power button and access the default wallet app.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eFor Pixel users, this will be Google Wallet, and should make accessing payment cards, concert tickets, and other items more seamless. Rahman does go on to state that since the wallet settings are configurable, this could also be used to quickly access the user\u0026#39;s digital wallet of choice. Regardless, if this does happen to find its way onto Android, it will provide a new and more convenient way to access a digital wallet on Android.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHowever, Rahman does state that he is unsure how and when Google will implement this feature. So it\u0026#39;s probably a good idea to forget about this feature until it arrives in a more substantial form. But, if it does manage to find it\u0026#39;s way into a build and becomes a public feature, it should be a great addition to the OS.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n    \n        \n\n    \n\n        \n\n\n                \n        \n        \n\n\n        \n\n\n\n\n\n                    \n        \n    \u003c/article\u003e\n\n    \n            \n        \u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
